cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with physical layer multicasting in wireless systems, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the coordination of interference among different cells and multicast groups, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of multi-antenna systems and the optimization of group-rates suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and game theory (cs.GT).
